From be33fd2edf55ee1ca2ca00d02fb4f8491a1eab90 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@becurious.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Apr 2026 15:32:11 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] Add Week view: full-week overview with all days side by side
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds a 📆 Week button between Daily and Audit. The week view shows
all active days (Sun–Thu) in a color-coded column grid. Each day
column contains car sections with compact session cards:

- Green = single drops (teacher color-coded left border)
- Blue = double/triple drops with all students listed
- Purple = group sessions with child count
- Orange (faded) = pickups

Each day header shows totals (drops, pickups, unique students) and
a footer shows active teachers and cars. Cars display their capacity
percentage. A branch filter dropdown scopes the view.

The layout is designed for quick visual scanning of the entire week
at a glance — no scrolling between days.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
